FBIS4-64461 "drweu086_h_94005" FBIS-WEU-94-086 Daily Report 3 May 1994 GERMANY Ruehe Says U.S. Understands Bundeswehr Cuts Ruehe Says U.S. Understands Bundeswehr Cuts LD0305124894 Berlin N-TV in German 1000 GMT 3 May 94 LD0305124894 Berlin N-TV German BFN [Text] The United States regards the planned deployment of crisis reaction forces made up of Bundeswehr soldiers and voluntary conscripts as a strengthening of Germany's ability to act. This was stated by German Defense Minister Volker Ruehe following talks with his U.S. counterpart William Perry. The German defense minister has attributed to the United States and Germany a decisive role in bringing about more stable international relations. The Americans have expressed understanding for Germany's plans to reduce the Bundeswehr to 300,000 men, Ruehe said. Apart from Germany's armed forces reform plans, the situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina and relations with Russia were also discussed in the talks. Ruehe will continue his U.S visit with a speech at the West Point Military Academy and a troop inspection at Fort Bragg.
